```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "partition": "short",
    "job_name": "ABQIH",
    "output_file": "qual.out",
    "error_file": "qual.err",
    "wall_time_limit": "0-05:00:00",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 28,
    "modules": [
      "easybuild",
      "prl",
      "python/3.6.0"
    ],
    "script": "Qual_Index_Swp.py",
    "arguments": [
      "-r1",
      "/projects/bgmp/2017_sequencing/1294_S1_L008_R1_001.fastq",
      "-r2",
      "/projects/bgmp/2017_sequencing/1294_S1_L008_R4_001.fastq",
      "-i1",
      "/projects/bgmp/2017_sequencing/1294_S1_L008_R2_001.fastq",
      "-i2",
      "/projects/bgmp/2017_sequencing/1294_S1_L008_R3_001.fastq",
      "-indf",
      "/home/abubie/qual_ind_swp/index.tsv",
      "-q_cut",
      "35"
    ],
    "working_directory": "/home/abubie/qual_ind_swp"
  }
}
```

This script is running on a **Slurm** workload manager. It defines several parameters for the job, including the partition, job name, output and error files, wall clock time limit, node count, and tasks per node. It then loads several modules: easybuild, prl, and python/3.6.0. 

The script runs a Python script named "Qual_Index_Swp.py" with several arguments related to fastq files and an index file. Finally, it echoes a message indicating the completion of the analysis.
